editorialSummary.text: Prime USDA-approved steaks and seafood, plus martinis and wine presented in a cozy, sophisticated setting.

originalText.text: First, I'll say that the ribeye was perfect. Perfectly cooked in the inside with a nice crispy crust and the fat was perfectly rendered. The sea bass was excellent as well, no complaints there at all. The crab cakes were decent as well. The Mac and cheese and asparagus were pretty average. My biggest complaint was just the chip ice in the old fashioned.

originalText.text: The restaurant is great. The food is delicious fairly large portion size and can also be split. Loved the crab cake and steak. Service was quick and the employees were attentive.

originalText.text: This amazing experience started off with Adam greeting us with a warm heart and showing us the dry age cooler on the way to the table. Then we were welcomed in by our expert waiter Ash. Words can't express how on point he was with suggestions, check-ins, timing, and professionalism. Very easy to chat with. Ceasar capped off the night by assisting with boxing our leftovers, and then Ash surprises us with an anniversary gift of New York Cheesecake!

originalText.text:
I really had to think hard about this review because it wasn't easy.
I want to start with the good part - the steak (bone in ribeye) was great.
But to be honest that's it.
I do understand that going out into a Steakhouse comes with some kind of premium. But if your prices are high i also want the quality to go with it.
There are no side dishes under 10 dollars. The broccoli costs 19 dollars - and to be really honest I have no idea why? It's broccoli and garlic. No finesse no new take on it. Just broccoli and garlic.
The fries are fine but the come with a 16 dollars price tag.
I probably wouldn't have brought this up when my check hadn't an automatic 18% tip included. (Btw nobody asked and it was nowhere mentioned before)
Which is not ok and they know it.
Price your items correctly so that u can pay your staff what they deserve (which with the prices you have should not be a problem).
So from my experience - yes the steak was good but everything else was just not up to any standard that comes with these price tags.
I want to stress the important point-i am absolutely willing to pay for great quality.
But royal 35 steakhouse just does not deliver on a 19 dollars broccoli dish or a 16 dollars French fries serving.
